notes: This side scan sonar image of the sea floor (120-350 m water depths) was mosaiced from data collected in 2002.An Edgetech DF1000 side scan system was used for geophysical surveying using only the 100Khz data. A Trimble DSM212Hdifferential GPS was used for positioning. Navigation from the GPS and gyro were logged in Hypack version 005B (CoastalOceanographics). Isis Sonar (Triton Imaging International) was used to log the digital sonar packets and cable counter data. Sonar data were captured using at an 150m range scale setting.
